jfm4vwoNJfrrr7xV9SgmfXNLjS535t-dE_dvwEdz4kZ_HdeY0Qw8fIQ0c-Fhe98gnadDCqZ0yMkRWkOphaWWMRtUdYjtQ-Q==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Figuring out startup tasks**\\n\\nI’m thinking we need to obey the startup requirements, and maybe the context already includes some files. I don’t clearly see any applicable skills, except perhaps self-improvement if a command fails unexpectedly. But before I respond, I need to scan the descriptions. Since this task involves running a watchdog script, it doesn't seem like there's a clear skill needed here. I might have to read the README and then execute the Python script.\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fDrMhBFpqqHYwcAEyOpWyp8B|fc_09f2f3d639446aff0169ca7184e480819098a5283581de4404","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\task_watchdog\\README.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\task_watchdog\\\\README.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":12222,"output":105,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12327,"cost":{"input":0.030555000000000002,"output":0.001575,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.032130000000000006}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774875008120,"responseId":"resp_09f2f3d639446aff0169ca7180ca108190af8fe6724f3d0f0d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6b6fdcd0","parentId":"95a1170b","timestamp":"2026-03-30T12:50:13.067Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_fDrMhBFpqqHYwcAEyOpWyp8B|fc_09f2f3d639446aff0169ca7184e480819098a5283581de4404","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Task Watchdog\n\nGlobal task registry + watchdog for Tobias long-running tasks.\n\n## Goal\n- track tasks launched by Tobias\n- check every 5 minutes\n- notify Lucca every 10 minutes while running\n- send final notification on completion/failure\n- stay silent when no tasks are active\n\n## Files\n- `config.json` — watchdog settings\n- `active_tasks.json` — active monitored tasks\n- `task_history.jsonl` — completed/failed task history\n- `watchdog.py` — deterministic status checker\n\n## Scope (MVP)\n- monitors Tobias-launched subagents first\n- stores global registry so it can work across chats/surfaces\n- internal timestamps are ISO; user-facing messages must be human formatted\n\n## Operational protocol (mandatory)\nFor every long-running subagent launched by Tobias:\n1. spawn the subagent\n2. immediately register it in `active_tasks.json`\n3. only after registration, confirm to Lucca that the task was launched\n\nRule:\n- spawn without register = incomplete launch\n- do not claim a task is being monitored unless it is already in the registry\n\n## Safety layers\nThe watchdog design uses three layers together:\n1. **Launch wrapper discipline** — spawn -> register -> confirm\n2. **No-confirmation-without-registry** — Tobias must not claim monitoring without persisted registration\n3. **Launch audit** — `watchdog_launch_audit.py` scans for recent unregistered subagent sessions and auto-registers them as a fallback safety net\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774875013041}}
